* Create Spring Boot Project
* Create Controllers with GetMapping and PostMapping - Test in browser and PostMan
* Add "springfox-boot-starter, swagger2,swagger-ui" dependency
* Enable Swagger documentation in spring application - "@EnableSwagger2"
* Run the application - "http://localhost:9000/swagger-ui/"
* you can see all controllers with all API's and error controller (we havent designed)
* Update/customize the api documentation - create configuration file

<dependency>
			<groupId>io.springfox</groupId>
			<artifactId>springfox-boot-starter</artifactId>
			<version>3.0.0</version>
		</dependency>
		<dependency>
			<groupId>io.springfox</groupId>
			<artifactId>springfox-swagger2</artifactId>
			<version>3.0.0</version>
		</dependency>
		<dependency>
			<groupId>io.springfox</groupId>
			<artifactId>springfox-swagger-ui</artifactId>
			<version>3.0.0</version>
		</dependency>


This dependency autowires whatever is necessary